org.orgName: United States District Court for the District of Washington

div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the District of Washington Northern Division.
div1.ab: In the Matter of the application of Lee Fong for a writ of habeas corpus.
United States of America, District of Washington,
div1.p: I, R. M. HOPKINS, Clerk of the District Court of the United States for the District of Washington, do hereby certify the attached and foregoing papers to be the original, and all of the original, papers on file and of record in my office at Seattle, Washington, in the above entitled court and cause, to-wit:
In witness whereof I have hereunto set my hand and official seal, at Seattle, Washington, this 6th day of September, 1902.
div1.ab: By H. M. Walthew Deputy Clerk.
IN THE Circuit Court OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
In the matter of the application of Lee Fong for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED IN THE U.S. CIRCUIT COURT, DIST. OF WASHINGTON. SEP 6 1902 A. REEVES AYRES, CLERK
